        "description": {
            "value": "<p>You know that there's no such thing as a true zero-gravity environment. You're sensitive to the ebbs and flows of microgravity and can use it to propel yourself even when you're floating @UUID[Compendium.sf2e.conditions.Item.Untethered]. When you're in an area of zero gravity, you gain a fly Speed of 30 feet, and you can Fly in zero gravity.</p><hr /><p><strong>Special</strong> You can use the @UUID[Compendium.sf2e.feats.Item.Weightless Defense] feat while Flying in zero gravity, even if you're not untethered. The benefits end if you stop Flying or leave zero gravity.</p>"
